entry.title: Putin Orders Military to Crush Wagner's Power Grab, Calls It Treason
entry.content: Russia’s president intervened after Yevgeny Prigozhin’s paramilitary group seized the city of Rostov and took positions inside the main military headquarters for southern Russia.

entry.title: What's Happening With Wagner in Russia?
entry.content: Putin is facing the most serious threat since he took power in 2000 as Wagner chief Yevgeny Prigozhin turns on Russia’s military establishment.
